# {{ project_name }}

A PyWeave application.

PyWeave gives you:

- Flask underneath
- Jinja as the primary templating language
- file-based backend routes in `app/pages`
- full SPA navigation without React Router, Vue Router, or any frontend router
- offline-first PWA support by default
- optional enhancement starters for Vue, React, Svelte, and Alpine

## Run locally

```bash
python -m venv .venv
source .venv/bin/activate
pip install -e .
pyweave dev
```

Open `http://127.0.0.1:5000`.

If you generated a Vue, React, Svelte, or Alpine-enhanced app, also run:

```bash
npm install
```

## Routes

Backend routes are created from files:

```txt
app/pages/index.py        -> /
app/pages/about.py        -> /about
app/pages/users/index.py  -> /users
app/pages/users/[id].py   -> /users/<id>
```

Each route returns template data. By convention, the matching Jinja template is loaded from `templates/pages`:

```python
def page():
    return {
        "title": "Home",
        "posts": [],
    }
```

This renders:

```txt
templates/pages/index.html
```

You can choose another template explicitly:

```python
def page():
    return {
        "template": "marketing/landing.html",
        "props": {"title": "Launch"},
    }
```

## Jinja SPA navigation

PyWeave intercepts internal links, requests the next Jinja page with `X-PyWeave`, swaps the HTML into the app shell, updates browser history, and keeps the same Flask/Jinja mental model.

You build pages with Jinja, but users experience app-like navigation.

## Optional component stacks

You can still create apps with optional component support:

```bash
pyweave new my-app --stack vue
pyweave new my-app --stack react
pyweave new my-app --stack svelte
pyweave new my-app --stack alpine
```

Jinja remains the primary rendering system. Component stacks are enhancement modes.

## PWA and offline-first SPA support

Every generated PyWeave app includes:

- `static/manifest.webmanifest`
- `static/sw.js` service worker
- `static/offline.html`
- app icons
- `static/pyweave-spa.js` for Jinja SPA navigation
- automatic offline route precaching via `/__pyweave/offline-manifest`

Static routes work offline after installation. Dynamic routes are cached after the first visit.
